        <h2><strong>Assignment Instructions</strong></h2>
        <p>For this activity, you will:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>Open a new notebook in <strong>Google Colab</strong> and give it a title that reflects <strong>Lesson 03 ‚Äî Variables</strong>.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Create variables to store information about your favorite athlete (e.g., <code>player_name = "LeBron James"</code>, <code>jersey_number = 23</code>, <code>points_per_game = 27.5</code>).</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Use descriptive variable names that follow Python naming conventions (lowercase with underscores, no spaces, must start with a letter).</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Practice assigning different data types to variables: strings (text), integers (whole numbers), and floats (decimal numbers).</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Update variable values by reassigning them (e.g., <code>points = 25</code> then <code>points = 30</code>) and print the results to see how variables can change.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Create a simple calculation using variables (e.g., calculate total points from field goals and free throws) and store the result in a new variable.</p>
